docs.snippet: Ethiopian police have arrested a blogger who criticized the government, especially its handling of the ongoing protests in the Oromia and Amhara regions.

headline.print_headline: Ethiopia Arrests Blogger, Academic Critical of Government
headline.main: Ethiopia Arrests Blogger, Academic Critical of Government

docs.snippet: Saudi-backed government forces and Iran-allied Houthis in Yemen accused each other of violating a ceasefire on Saturday as the United Nations tried to extend the three-day truce.

headline.print_headline: Fighting Rages in Yemen as U.N. Seeks to Extend 72-Hour Ceasefire
headline.main: Fighting Rages in Yemen as U.N. Seeks to Extend 72-Hour Ceasefire

docs.snippet: A member of the Swedish Academy that awarded the 2016 Nobel Prize in literature to Bob Dylan says the American singer-songwriter's silence since receiving the honor is "impolite and arrogant."

headline.print_headline: Nobel Academy Member Calls Bob Dylan's Silence 'Arrogant'
headline.main: Nobel Academy Member Calls Bob Dylan's Silence 'Arrogant'

docs.snippet: Apple says it will start offering cash rewards of up to $200,000 to hackers who come forward with information about security flaws in the company's software.

headline.print_headline: Apple to Offer Cash for Reporting Security Flaws
headline.main: Apple to Offer Cash for Reporting Security Flaws

docs.snippet: Lady Gaga is choosing the intimacy of dive bars over arenas to showcase songs from her new album, "Joanne."

headline.print_headline: Lady Gaga Picks Dive Bars Over Arenas to Introduce Album
headline.main: Lady Gaga Picks Dive Bars Over Arenas to Introduce Album

docs.snippet: The University of Mississippi chancellor on Friday condemned a student's online comment about lynching as "racist, offensive and hurtful" after dozens of other students said the chancellor's initial response to the comment was weak and insensitive...

headline.print_headline: Ole Miss Chancellor: Student's Lynching Comment Was 'Racist'
headline.main: Ole Miss Chancellor: Student's Lynching Comment Was 'Racist'

The owners of a German restaurant in New York have taken down an autographed photo of Donald Trump because they say it was hurting the business.

headline.main: Restaurant Takes Down Trump Photo Amid Yelp Complaints

docs.snippet: Police in Milwaukee, Wisconsin, on Thursday said the officer whose killing of a black man in August sparked nights of rioting has been arrested and charged with sexually assaulting another man just a day after the deadly shooting.

headline.print_headline: Milwaukee Officer Who Killed Black Man Charged With Sex Assault
headline.main: Milwaukee Officer Who Killed Black Man Charged With Sex Assault
